         <abstract>
            <p>Let $\mu_1,\ldots,\mu_k$ be odd positive integers and $n = \sum^k_{i=1}(\mu_i + 1)$. Let $\{u_i\}^n_{i=1}$ be an extended Tchebycheff system on $\lbrack a, b \rbrack$. Let $L$ be a positive linear functional on $U \equiv \operatorname{span}(\{u_i\})$. We prove that $L$ has a unique representation in the form $$L(p) = \sum_{i=1}^k \sum_{j=0}^{\mu_i -1} a_{ij}p^{(j)}(t_i), \quad a &lt; t_1 &lt; \cdots &lt; t_k &lt; b,$$ for all $p \in U$. The proof uses the topological degree of a mapping $F: \bar{D} \subset R^k \rightarrow R^k$. The result is proved by showing that the equation $F(\underline{t}) = 0$ has a unique solution, which in turn is proved by showing that $F$ has degree 1 and that for any solution $\underline{t}$ to the equation $F(\underline{t}) = 0 \det F'(\underline{t}) &gt; 0$. We also give extensions to the cases when the $\{u_i\}$ are a periodic extended Tchebycheff system and when $L$ is a nonnegative linear functional.</p>
